In this statement, Vice President Biden discusses the progress made in the bipartisan debt talks. He mentions that significant progress has been made in finding common ground and potential agreement on substantial savings. However, the next phase of the talks is in the hands of the leaders, who need to determine the scope of an agreement that can attract bipartisan support. The talks are currently on hold as they await guidance from the leaders. Vice President Biden emphasizes the need for a balanced approach that includes real savings across the budget, including domestic spending, defense spending, mandatory spending, and tax code loopholes. He also mentions that sacrifices need to be made by all, including the most fortunate. Vice President Biden expresses gratitude to the negotiators for taking on the challenge and highlights the importance of taking responsible steps to benefit the economy and the nation's future.